Program_Policies: A grade of C or better is required for all courses in the minor, as specified by Senate Policy 59-10. In addition, at least six credits of the minor must be unique from the prescribed courses required by a student's major(s).; BIOL 110 is a prerequisite for ANSC 211.; ANSC 100 is a prerequisite for ANSC 311.; ANSC 211, ANSC 311 and MICRB 106 & MICRB 107 or MICRB 201 & MICRB 202 are prerequisites for ANSC 425/VBSC 425.; ANSC 395 and ANSC 496 must have a poultry or avian biology emphasis.
